1	//! The interactive-UI **state machine**: route dispatch decisions, theory-version
2	//! management, and response-envelope assembly.
3	//!
4	//! This is the web layer's *behaviour* — what each route returns — as opposed to
5	//! the round-1/round-2 template modules (which produce the bytes of individual
6	//! bodies). It is parameterised over a [`ProverOps`] callback trait supplied at
7	//! integration by the ported prover; this module never inspects the theory, it
8	//! only decides which callback to invoke, how the version state changes, and how
9	//! to wrap the resulting fragment into an HTTP response.
10	//!
11	//! Everything here was derived from black-box observation (see `BEHAVIOR.md` §13
12	//! and `QUERIES.log` [Q029]–[L16]); no prover source was read.
13	//!
14	//! ## Observed semantics reproduced here
15	//! * **Version model.** Version 1 is the originally loaded theory; every *proof*
16	//!   operation (`main/method`, `autoprove`) allocates a fresh monotonically
17	//!   increasing index (`= previous max + 1`) and leaves earlier versions
18	//!   resolvable, whereas every *structural* edit (`edit`/`add`/`delete` lemma)
19	//!   mutates the theory **in place** at the requested index (no new index). Pure
20	//!   navigation and views never change the version set.
21	//! * **Envelopes.** Proof operations answer `200` with a JSON `{"redirect":URL}`
22	//!   pointing at `overview/proof/{lemma}/{focus}` of the new version. Structural
23	//!   POSTs answer `303 See Other` with a `Location` header (POST-redirect-GET) and
24	//!   an empty body; a *failed* structural edit instead answers `200` re-rendering
25	//!   the full-page form. `next`/`prev` answer `text/plain` with a bare URL.
26	//! * **Paths.** A proof path is the raw `/`-join of case-name segments (root `_`);
27	//!   segments are prover identifiers (`[A-Za-z0-9_]`), never percent-encoded. The
28	//!   focus path in a proof-op redirect is the prover's next open goal.
29	
